Key Match Events: England slumped to 52 for 4 in the chase
Liam Livingstone briefly sparkled with the bat but his departure ended any hope of England drawing first blood
Miscellaneous Highlights: More than 1,000 solar panels were turned on for the first time in Hampshire’s bid to become the world’s greenest cricket stadium
Others: Australia were without the retired David Warner and several of their rested multi-format stars
Three debutants in Jordan Cox, Jacob Bethell and Jamie Overton played for England
